Creating Visual Card 11

Adding Visual  card for Violation Per month, and YOY

Steps

Violation Per Month Visual Card

  1.        Open Visualization Pane
  2.        Select  Visual Card
  3.        Drag the visual on to the dashboard
  4.        Click on Violation Per Month Measure and place it inside the fields
  5.        General: X - Position = 0, Y - Position = 303, Width = 205, Height = 97
  6.        Data Label : Color = #000000,  Font Size = 30,  Font type = DIN
  7.        Category = OFF
  8.        Title ON ,   Text Title = "Violation Per Month", Font Color = #FFFFFF , Background Color = #073501 , Font Size = 14 and Font Family = DIN
  9.        Border ON, Color = #E6E6E6 , Radius = 0



Steps

YOY

  1.        Open Visualization Pane
  2.        Select  Visual Card
  3.        Drag the visual on to the dashboard
  4.        Click on YOY and place it inside the fields
  5.        General: X - Position = 0, Y - Position = 407, Width = 205, Height = 97
  6.        Data Label : Color =#D9B300,  Font Size = 30,  Font type = DIN
  7.        Category = OFF
  8.        Title ON ,   Text Title = "%YOY Violation", Font Color = #FFFFFF , Background Color = #073501 , Font Size = 14 and Font Family = DIN
  9.           Border ON, Color = #E6E6E6 , Radius = 0



Steps

YOY Indicator 

  1.        Open Visualization Pane
  2.        Select  Visual Card
  3.        Drag the visual on to the dashboard
  4.        Click on Indicator YOY and place it inside the fields
  5.        General: X - Position = 146, Y - Position = 443, Width = 59, Height = 50
  6.        Data Label : Font Size = 30,  Font type = DIN, Color:  IF YOY > 0 the Data Color will be #BB0412    OR   IF YOY < 0  the Data Color will be #05750E

       7.        Category = OFF


Indicator Data Label Color Depend on the the value of the value of YOY 
       Click on Data Label then click on the Data Label Color Function 

               IF YOY > 0 the Data Color will be #BB0412

               IF YOY < 0  the Data Color will be #05750E
